Independent examination or independent exam refers to a special type of interim assessment held outside the framework of any specific course and aimed at monitoring the level of key learning outcomes acquired by students, as stipulated by HSE University’s educational standard and/or a given degree programme. One or several courses of the degree programme may serve as prerequisites for an independent examination. Decisions during an independent examination will be made:
- by a board composed of several teachers, preferably including those who did not take part in delivering prerequisite courses to students;
- using automated e-learning tools and/or remote technology, coupled with mandatory proctoring (face-to-face or online).

