Individual categories of students refer to students whose initial educational opportunities and/or special status affect the pace and quality of their studies under degree programmes, i.e.:
students with disabilities and/or health conditions;
students and individuals belonging to the category of orphans and children left without parental care, as well as individuals who lost both or only parents during their studies;
students who are either participants in the Special Military Operation (hereinafter, the “SMO”) or their immediate relatives;
students who are citizens of foreign countries;
students admitted to study at HSE University in the relevant year who are subject to special aspects for conducting the Final State Certification (FSC) for general education programmes at the secondary level and for admission to study at higher educational institutions, as stipulated by Article 5 of Federal Law No. 19-FZ, dated February 17, 2023 “On Special Aspects of the Legal Regulation of Education and Science in Connection With the Admission of the Donetsk People's Republic, Lugansk People's Republic, Zaporozhye Region, and Kherson Region to the Russian Federation, and Amendments to Specific Legislative Acts of the Russian Federation.”

